        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Currently, when using sub controllers in the default module, a helper path based on the leading path segment is created, instead of using the default. For example:\n{code}\napplication\/\n    controllers\/\n        Admin\/\n            FooController.php\n    views\/\n        helpers\/\n            SomeHelper.php\n{code}\napplication\/views\/helpers\/SomeHelper.php would contain the class Zend_View_Helper_SomeHelper. If an action in Admin_FooController is invoked and the view calls the someHelper() helper, it will attempt to resolve it to Admin_View_Helper_SomeHelper and not find it."
        },
